{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17582966","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17582966"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:02:28+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:02:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1619"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1619","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1619"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1619"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"26209"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1619","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1619"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1619"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"13444"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"552"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"}]},"contributions":{"data":[]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"26209","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/26209"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA foreign body can be seen in this plain abdominal radiograph of a 42-year-old woman (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the underlying disease process?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Munchausen syndrome","Obesity","Obstructing oesophageal cancer","Refractory ascites","Metastatic breast cancer"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWhilst this looks like a foreign body within the stomach and the diagnosis of deliberate self-harm or attention-seeking (Munchausen syndrome) might come to mind, the structure is a gastric band. It has been inserted to help try and manage \u003Cstrong\u003Eobesity\u003C/strong\u003E. The use of gastric bands has now been superseded by roux-en-y gastric bypass and gastric sleeve surgery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther foreign materials encountered at this site could include an oesophageal mesh stent, used for the management of malignant dysphagia. Sometimes shunts can be inserted to help manage refractory ascites, resistant to standard medical therapies (LeVeen shunt). Such a shunt would be seen to be extending up into the chest (anterior chest wall). The site is rather too low for any of the subcutaneous intravenous infusions used used for chemotherapy for metastatic disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Gastric bands are no longer the standard of surgical care for obesity."],"references":["Magouliotis DE, Tasiopoulou VS, Svokos AA, et al. Roux-En-Y Gastric Bypass versus Sleeve Gastrectomy as Revisional Procedure after Adjustable Gastric Band: a Systematic Review and Meta-Analysis.  Surg. 2017; 27:1365-73."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"13444"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1619"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"16296"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"16296","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/16296"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/bc4e5c22-e452-4f07-a97f-8ef31e69cc7f.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/bc4e5c22-e452-4f07-a97f-8ef31e69cc7f.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":720,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"13444","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/13444"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2022-08-02T14:59:43+09:30","updatedAt":"2022-08-02T14:59:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1619"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"26209"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"